Clini-Therm Corp said a Dallas courtgranted a temporary restraining order prohibiting a formerofficer and director from using or disclosing privelegedinformation obtained during employment at the company.    The 95th Judicial District Court of Dallas County set ahearing on April 8 to consider a preliminary injunction, thecompany said.    The court ordered the former officer, Victor Vaguine, toappear at the hearing and show cause why he should not beenjoined from working for BSD Medical Corp, the company said. Reuter&#3;